Release Notes
Sigma Trinity Model

Sigma Trinity Model is an open-source Pine Script strategy designed to study how structural regime logic, continuation entries, and coordinated stop management can operate within a single position model.

The script integrates three components that operate under one shared position state:

1) Structural Regime (Rasta Module)

Market structure is defined using:

A primary EMA of a user-selected source

A secondary smoothing layer (SMA, EMA, RMA, WMA, or None applied to that EMA)

A long condition begins when the primary EMA crosses above its smoothed derivative.
A short condition begins on the inverse crossover.

This crossover defines regime bias rather than repeated signal firing. Only one directional state can be active at a time. Optional EMA 8/21 filtering can restrict entries to broader trend alignment.

2) Continuation Entries (Pyramid Module)

The Pyramid module is optional and operates only when a structural position is already active.

It uses a separate EMA/smoothing configuration to allow additional entries in the direction of the active regime. It cannot initiate new regime direction independently. This ensures continuation logic remains subordinate to the primary structural condition.

3) Integrated Stop Logic

Risk management is handled internally using:

A configurable fixed stop

An optional trailing stop

Optional trigger thresholds

Wick or close-based stop detection

Optional buffer percentage

The trailing stop activates only after price moves a defined distance from entry and ratchets in the favorable direction without widening. Fixed and trailing logic resolve into a single exit event.

Strategy Defaults

The script uses:

Initial capital: 10,000

Order size: 10% of equity

Commission: 0.25%

Slippage: 3

Pyramiding: up to 3 entries

Users may adjust these properties in the Strategy Settings panel. Backtest results depend on market, timeframe, and configuration.

How to Use

Apply the script to a price chart (overlay).

Users can configure:

EMA lengths and smoothing type

EMA 8/21 filter behavior

Long-only, short-only, or bidirectional mode

Fixed and trailing stop parameters

Pyramid module activation

The script is intended for analytical study of structured entry and exit coordination within Pine Script. It does not provide financial advice.
